HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1568
By Hulsey
A RESOLUTION to recognize Grace Bonecutter on the occasion
of her retirement as an employee of the
Tennessee General Assembly.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that we should honor those valuable legislative employees
who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their years of
meritorious service to the General Assembly; and
WHEREAS, Grace Bonecutter is one such estimable person, who has served with
distinction as an exemplary employee of the General Assembly and will be taking her much-
deserved retirement in 2026; and
WHEREAS, a lifelong resident of Clarksville, Grace Bonecutter is a graduate of Austin
Peay State University, where she was a member of Chi Omega Fraternity; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Bonecutter began her illustrious career with the State of Tennessee in
on August 15, 2005, as an employee of the Division of Elections for the Secretary of State, a
position she held for almost seven years; and
WHEREAS, Grace Bonecutter joined the General Assembly in February 2012 to work in
the office of Representative Terri Lynn Weaver, where she would continue to serve until 2022,
when she began her current tenure in the office of Representative Bud Hulsey; and
WHEREAS, during her legislative career, Mrs. Bonecutter has also served as staff for
both the House Transportation Committee (108th-112th General Assemblies) and the House
Criminal Justice Committee (113th General Assembly); and
WHEREAS, during her distinguished career with the legislature, Grace Bonecutter has
displayed the utmost professionalism, always speaking kindly and respectfully to everyone; she
is a deeply caring and considerate person and one of the most knowledgeable and experienced
HJR1568
018535
- 1 -

legislative assistants; a mentor to all, she will be sorely missed by her friends and coworkers so
very much; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of her excellence as a legislative employee, Grace Bonecutter
was named House Employee of the Year in 2020; and
WHEREAS, she is grateful for the love and support she shares with her husband of
more than fifty years, Hank; her children and their spouses, Kathryn and Austin Hall and Seth
and Scottie Bonecutter; and her grandchildren, Olivia, Bryce, Owen, and Beau; and
WHEREAS, a woman of deep and abiding faith, she has been a devoted member of
First Baptist Church in Clarksville since she was a young girl; and
WHEREAS, in her retirement, she will undoubtedly have more time to spend with her
family, especially her treasured grandchildren, avidly support the Nashville Predators, and
discover more great lunch spots; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Bonecutter exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and
community that are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, throughout her estimable career, Grace Bonecutter has demonstrated the
utmost professionalism, ability, and integrity, winning the unbridled respect and admiration of
her colleagues and the leadership and members of the General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we extend to Grace Bonecutter our heartfelt wishes for a happy and
fulfilling retirement and every continued success in her future endeavors and thank her for her
dedicated and efficient service to the General Assembly.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
